What is Draft:
______________
The draft features allows users to temporarily save changes to the BO, without immediately persisting them to the DB.
Draft table is should be same as root entity- this is automatically create that.
for enahncement of the root entity- -> added the new fields to exist root entity --> in draft table also add those fields explicitly.( recreate option will come if added new fields at root enity)
- so last changed field added .. to draft table also.
draft feature automatically handles to update the create/update/delete the records draft table.

Odata V2 and Odata-v4 differnece:(Service Binding )
__________________________________
in Odata V2 managed scenario - Draft handling automatically...
in Odata V4 managed scenario - Manually need to add for Draft handling...

Scenario: Can i able to add draft functionality in Odata V4 binding?(With out draft)
___________________________________________________________________
in Odata v4 draft is the default transition pattern. if draft is not defined, the framework assumes read-only. means no create/update.. that's why buttons doon't showup.
in Odata v4 - if draft functionality not availble then Fiori Apps show only the Read and delete functionality available.- in object page, unable to see the update functionality also.

With draft:
__________
RAP amanges a temporarly "working copy" of the entity --> UI automatically shows create/Update/Save/cancel buttons.


